The paper deals with human video motion transfer, which involves computer vision and graphics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions appearance control, which involves generating new appearances by altering input appearance information, indicating the use of machine learning techniques. This makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which are commonly used in image and video generation tasks, indicating the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.GR (Graphics).
